Step 1: Locate `default` branches in `switch` statements that are not in the last position.

Step 2: Move the `default` case to the end of the switch block, ensuring the execution order semantics remain unchanged.

Step 3: If there are fall-through cases (missing `break` statements), handle with caution during automated refactoring:
- First insert a `// WARNING: fall-through case - manual review required` comment
- Do not automatically rearrange such cases to avoid altering control flow
